# Database: Use Drizzle ORM Exclusively

All database interactions **must** go through Drizzle ORM. Never use raw SQL strings, the `neon` SQL tag directly, or any other query method.

## Setup

- DB client: `db` exported from [`src/lib/db.ts`](mdc:src/lib/db.ts)
- Schema tables: `decks`, `cards`, `cardReviews` (+ enum `reviewResultEnum`) in [`src/lib/schema.ts`](mdc:src/lib/schema.ts)

## Usage

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — Drizzle query
import { db } from "@/lib/db";
import { decks } from "@/lib/schema";
import { eq } from "drizzle-orm";

const userDecks = await db.select().from(decks).where(eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId));

// ✅ GOOD — insert
await db.insert(cards).values({ deckId, front, back });

// ✅ GOOD — update
await db.update(decks).set({ title }).where(eq(decks.id, deckId));

// ✅ GOOD — delete
await db.delete(cards).where(eq(cards.id, cardId));
```

```ts
// ❌ BAD — raw SQL
const sql = neon(process.env.DATABASE_URL!);
const rows = await sql`SELECT * FROM decks WHERE clerk_user_id = ${userId}`;
```

## Schema Changes

- Add or modify tables/columns **only** in `src/lib/schema.ts`
- After schema changes, generate and apply migrations:
  ```bash
  npx drizzle-kit generate
  npx drizzle-kit migrate
  ```
- Never manually edit files in the `drizzle/` migrations folder
